<section class="about-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
      <h2>Why Payxem Exists</h2>
      <p>Most financial tools are not built for independent workers.</p>
      <p>They are built for large companies, complex accounting, or regions where payment systems already work smoothly.</p>
      <p>That leaves millions of freelancers and small businesses dealing with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Limited access to global payment systems</li>
        <li>Complicated invoicing tools</li>
        <li>High fees and unnecessary subscriptions</li>
        <li>Scattered workflows across multiple platforms</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="emphasis">Payxem was built to fix this.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
      <h2>What Payxem Does</h2>
      <p>Payxem gives you a simple system to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Create professional invoices</li>
        <li>Share payment links</li>
        <li>Track payments and earnings</li>
        <li>Manage your financial activity in one place</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Payments are handled through trusted providers like PayPal and Stripe, while Payxem focuses on structure, clarity, and control.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
      <h2>How Payxem Works</h2>
      <p>Payxem is designed as a coordination and tracking layer around real payment systems.</p>
      <p>When your client pays, the transaction is processed through trusted third-party providers. Payxem then records, organizes, and reflects that activity inside your dashboard so you can clearly see what you have earned, what is pending, and what is available.</p>
      <p>In some cases, payments may be received into accounts managed by Payxem or its affiliated entities for settlement and distribution. The goal is to make the flow simple for you, without requiring you to manage multiple systems manually.</p>
      <p>Payxem itself does not operate as a bank or a payment processor. It focuses on giving you visibility, structure, and control over your financial activity.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

